At home:

	Compile command;
	$ mpic++ -o run main.cpp bath_setup.cpp density.cpp propagation.cpp transition_matrix.cpp -lgsl -lgslcblas -lm -std=c++11

	Run command:
	$ mpirun -n 10 ./run
	(Note: Put the number of processors you want to use after '-n')



On HPC Clusters (example ICHEC Fionn Ireland):
    Modules;
    $ module load libs gsl/intel/2.3
    $ module load dev intel/2017-u3

    Compile command;
    $ mpiicpc -o run main.cpp bath_setup.cpp density.cpp propagation.cpp transition_matrix.cpp -lgsl -lgslcblas -lm -std=c++11
